   <refnamediv>
       <refname>param_g </refname>
               <refpurpose>determines the font parameters </refpurpose>
   </refnamediv>
 
        <refsynopsisdiv>
               <title>CALLING SEQUENCE</title>
               <synopsis>param_g(ref_nbinter,thresh,font_axis)</synopsis>
        </refsynopsisdiv>
 
        <refsection>
           <title>PARAMETERS</title>
           <variablelist>
           <varlistentry>
 
           <term>Input</term>
 
 
<listitem><para>*  <term> ref_nbinter </term> =    # of chars that can be drawn on the x axis</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>*  <term> thresh </term> =    # of chars in the title that causes a decline of 1 unit in the title font</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>*  <term> font_axis</term>  =    font of the axes</para></listitem>
 
 
 
<listitem><para>&#160;</para></listitem>
 
           </varlistentry>
 
          <varlistentry>
 
          <term>Output</term>
 
<listitem><para>* nothing: the parameters in saved in a scilab database</para></listitem>
 
 
          </varlistentry>
          </variablelist>
        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
 Set the values useful to set titles and axes that are readable. Default values suitable for one type of screen cannot be so for others: if this is the case, the user has to enter, by trial and error, the values suitable to her.
 
        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>EXAMPLE</title>
              <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
param_g(60,12,11,4)
// Set the default values.
param_g(40,9,8,3)
// Set values suitable for smaller screens.
 
               ]]></programlisting>
        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>AUTHOR</title>
Eric Dubois 2002
        </refsection>
</refentry>
